##A number of public officers have been reprimanded in Guangyuan after citizens gathered to take off masks and drink tea

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Zhong Yuhao, reporter, thepaper.cn

Recently, Guangyuan, Sichuan Province has been getting a lot of attention for its citizens gathering to take off masks and drink dam tea. The latest news on February 23 shows that, zhang Dong, director of the square service center of the Guangyuan Urban Management Law Enforcement Bureau, and others involved in the issue were put on file for investigation by the Party discipline and the government.

Previously, on February 20, Guangyuan issued the 18th public notice of the Emergency Response Headquarters for the epidemic of COVID-19 pneumonia, the fourth point of the notice was raised, according to chinanews.com, in the tea houses, bathing and health care, sports and fitness, beauty and health care, amusement places and other five types of businesses that have been temporarily closed for business as required by the announcement No. 2 of the Municipal Headquarters, the business of outdoor dam tea, outdoor sports and outdoor amusement places shall be resumed, nail Salon is allowed to open, other commercial form of business outlets have been suspended business should immediately resume business.

However, the announcement issued the next day, as part of the business recovery, many places, especially in urban areas have a large number of people gathered. Among them, Guangyuan Lizhou District Plaza Dam tea attracted a large number of people gathered, business is booming. Later, a video showing Guangyuan residents unloading masks and drinking dam tea caught the attention of netizens across the country.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Video capture

At 1900 hours on February 21, Guangyuan's emergency response headquarters for the COVID-19 pneumonia outbreak announced that with the recovery of some business forms, a large number of people have gathered in many places, especially in urban areas. The Municipal Emergency Command Department reminded the general public that the epidemic situation is still in the stage I emergency response period of a major public health emergency, and the risk of spreading the epidemic is relatively high. People should stay away from gathering places and not participate in gathering activities, wear a mask in crowded places. Each outdoor business to increase the distance between the business stalls, each stall edge to maintain more than 1.5 meters away, and do a good job in the management of the killing site. Urban Management Law enforcement, market supervision departments and grass-roots communities to strengthen supervision and management, serious violations of regulations, according to law to be punished.

At 2200 hours on February 22, the Guangyuan Emergency Response Headquarters for COVID-19 pneumonia issued a new announcement: in view of the current severe situation of the prevention and control of the new coronavirus epidemic, in order to effectively guard against the possible risk of the spread of the new coronavirus brought about by the gathering of personnel, the relevant matters are announced below. Football, basketball and volleyball in outdoor sports will be suspended. Square dancing, Rouliqiu and other group cultural and sports activities will be prohibited. Mahjong, playing cards and other recreational activities in business premises and public places will be prohibited Enterprises and institutions shall not hold any non-productive activities of an aggregate nature.

The paper noted that on February 22, Zou Zijing, deputy secretary of the CPC Guangyuan Municipal Committee and Mayor, stressed that the city was still in the stage I emergency response period for major public health emergencies, while investigating the recovery of the catering industry and open-air commercial operations in the city proper, the spread of the epidemic risk is greater, departments at all levels should continue to maintain high vigilance, strict prevention of personnel gathering. He pointed out that restaurants are allowed to provide in-room food, but must strictly adopt such methods as dining at separate tables, maintain a safe distance, strictly control the flow of customers and resolutely avoid the gathering of people. Must strengthen the dining place ventilation, suspends the use air conditioning, the scientific standard completes the internal disinfection disinfection work, maintains the customer dining place security hygiene tidiness.

The report also said that Zou Zijing was very concerned about how to effectively reduce the risk of the spread of the epidemic and ensure the health and safety of the people after the outdoor dam tea and outdoor amusement places resumed business. He visited the Water Park, Jialing Plaza, Qianfoya scenic area and Lantau Peak Park to see for himself the setting up of the outdoor tea shop and the implementation of preventive and control measures. Zou Zijing requested that outdoor businesses should strictly implement the requirements of the municipal emergency headquarters, expand the space between business stalls and prevent people from gathering. To strengthen the consumption environment and tea drinking utensils cleaning and disinfection, to ensure consumer food safety. To strengthen the public's advice, strictly prohibited in the dam tea stalls playing Mahjong, playing cards. The urban management law enforcement, market supervision departments and grass-roots organizations should strengthen supervision and management to ensure that the gathering of personnel does not occur.

According to Sichuan online February 23 news, Guangyuan 6 confirmed cases of new pneumonia patients were all cured and discharged, 20 consecutive days no new confirmed cases of pneumonia, there are suspected cases of zero cases, 10 people are under medical observation.
